  <bioghist id="aspace_227324d7a8911de26b9ff009a4bfe2cb">
    <head>Biography</head>
<p>Charles Gardner Hall was born in 1888 and attended Connecticut Agricultural College. He was the doorkeeper of Connecticut House of Representatives and a farmer living in Mansfield Center, CT. Charles Gardner Hall also served in the House of Representative as a Republican, representing Mansfield for two terms (1947 and 1949). Gardner died in 1969.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_2152866c1aa62db575bc7e51b0326f67">
    <head>Scope and Content</head>
<p>The Charles G. Hall Papers contain correspondence, diaries, family papers, scrapbooks, photographs, publications, and other papers, relating to Hall's personal life, student days at Connecticut Agricultural College, activities as doorkeeper of Connecticut House of Representatives, state politics, events at University of Connecticut>, and family affairs.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <arrangement id="aspace_bcaa9e3cb2294a7f4fccb884dae22cd8">
    <head>Arrangement</head>
<p><emph render="bold">Series I: Diaries </emph> (1888-1969) consists of fifty-three diaries written by Charles G. Hall and his family members. The entries detail daily occurrences and reports of the weather. Also included in this section is a diary written by Hall's' aunt, Julie Hall Brown, during the year of his birth (1889).</p><p><emph render="bold">Series II: Personal Papers</emph>  (undated, 1828-1972) contains correspondence primarily received from Hall's political colleagues. Also included are Hall's General Assembly bills regarding smoking in bed and injuries incurred in state parks and forests (1949), two scrapbooks of newspaper clippings (1914); legal papers and Germaine Hall's composition book (1934)</p><p><emph render="bold">Series III: Photographs</emph> (undated, 1905-1965) contains photographs of Charles G. Hall in various classes and in the dormitory at Connecticut Agricultural College. Other photographs focus on University of Connecticut events and the House of Representatives with Hall as doorkeeper.</p><p><emph render="bold">Series IV: General Assembly</emph> (1915-1951) consists of two reports by the Claims Committee (1947, 1949) and General Assembly publications which include: <title render="italic">Manual and Role of the General Assembly</title> (1915), <title render="italic">Calendar for the House of Representatives</title> (1915), an address by the clerk of the House (146), a booklet entitled <title render="italic">Information for Connecticut Legislators</title> and a directory of the 1951 General Assembly and elected state officials.</p>  </arrangement>
  <separatedmaterial id="aspace_1e4850de8dc92a77b5732ea067bdb672">
    <head>Separated Material</head>
<p>The following materials have been separated from the collection and cataloged:</p><p><title render="italic">Address by Dwight D. Eisenhower</title>. Dodd Call No.</p><p><title render="italic">Addresses by the Honorable Paul G. Hoffman</title>. Dodd Call No.</p><p><title render="italic">Almanac</title>. Dodd Call No.</p><p><title render="italic">Birds of Storrs and Vicinity</title>. Dodd Call No.</p><p><title render="italic">Birth of a Nation</title>. Dodd Call No.</p><p><title render="italic">Connecticut Register</title>. Dodd Periodicals</p><p><title render="italic">Connecticut's Old Houses</title>. Dodd Call No.</p><p><title render="italic">Family Fall-Out Shelters</title>. Dodd Call No.</p><p><title render="italic">Highlights of the Byrd Antarctica Expedition</title>. Dodd Call No.</p><p><title render="italic">Law Making in Connecticut</title>. Dodd Call No.</p><p><title render="italic">Old Farmer's Almanac</title>. Dodd Call No.</p><p><title render="italic">Outline of Government in Connecticut</title>. Dodd Call No.</p><p><title render="italic">Picturesque America</title>. Dodd Call No.</p><p><title render="italic">Pocket Manual</title>. Dodd Periodicals</p><p><title render="italic">State Employees Retirement Act</title>. Dodd Call No.</p><p>University of Connecticut materials (president's newsletters, bulletins of Connecticut Agricultural College, and other university and college publications), State of <geogname>Connecticut</geogname> publications have been integrated into the periodical collections.</p><p>Photographs and postcards have been relocated to the University Photograph Collection. The SCrapbook has been relocated to the University Scrapbook Collection (1979_0006_scpb_1).</p>  </separatedmaterial>
